The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 29 (PTI): The information and broadcasting ministry has issued a show-cause notice to Colors channel for its serial Rishton Se Badi Pratha, claiming that it portrays excessive violence.          
	The ministry asked the channel to explain within a week why the show does not violate the Cable Act. The show is about a couple who decide to marry against the wishes of their family.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The Central Administrative Tribunal has urged the government to speed up proceedings against employees facing charges of misconduct. It was hearing a plea by a Delhi Development Authority official, who had not been charged for four years in a corruption case.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): A Delhi court has sentenced a former CBI officer to six years in prison for accepting a bribe from a Hindustan Petroleum employee in a trap laid by the probe agency in 2004. M.S. Sisodiya, a former CBI inspector, had been found with Rs 25,000 in cash.                   
	 Bhopal (PTI): An engineering student has been arrested for hacking bank accounts to book railway and air tickets. A police officer said Sunny Kumar, 20, had made the bookings for friends and acquaintances offering them large discounts.                   
	Bhopal (PTI): A local court has rejected a plea for bail by a senior police officer and his wife, who are accused of demanding dowry from their daughter-in-law. Ajit Kumar Shrivastava and Manjulata allegedly harassed their daughter-in-law Namrata for Rs 30 lakh.                   
	Bhopal (PTI): A 22-year-old teacher allegedly hanged herself at her residence on Tuesday. Police said the family of Shilpi Raut, who was crowned Miss Bhopal last year, found her hanging from a ceiling fan when they returned from an outing. Shilpi had been teaching at Kanian School.
                                                                                                                                              
